\label{sec:meth}

\subsection{Study Design}
\paragraph{Participants} A total of $n= 98$ participants were recruited using reddit ($n=32$) and Amazon Mechanical Turk ($n=63$). Participants were required to be over 18. We collected information about their age range, gender, and education levels. Compared to demographics of the general US population \citep[as published in][]{census2016} we see in \autoref{fig:demographics2} that survey participants are generally younger and more highly educated. This effect is even more pronounced amoung participants recruited from reddit than amazon turkers. In addition, redditors are slightly more likely to identify as male or non-binary gender. Reddit participants were recruited from two subreddits which are data and visualization related, and therefore might be expected to be more educated and proficient at reading charts and graphs than the general population; they were also volunteers and did not receive any remuneration, where Amazon Mechanical Turk users receive some minimal compensation for their participation. 


